1
00:01:50,160 --> 00:01:51,320
Shang Ningyu.

2
00:01:51,880 --> 00:01:53,680
It's already the second semester of sophomore year.

3
00:01:53,680 --> 00:01:55,360
Why aren't you doing your homework?

4
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:56,440
I'm telling you,

5
00:01:56,640 --> 00:01:59,170
Ruirui is studying extremely hard right now.

6
00:01:59,240 --> 00:02:00,680
If you don't make progress,

7
00:02:00,680 --> 00:02:02,200
be careful she might look down on you in the future.

8
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,440
That's impossible.

9
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:05,690
Ruirui isn't such a superficial girl.

10
00:02:05,840 --> 00:02:08,080
She will definitely see my inner depth.

11
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:10,320
Doesn't Ruirui like drinking soda?

12
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:11,360
Happy back to school.

13
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,020
I brought some for you two too.

14
00:02:15,160 --> 00:02:16,240
Awesome.

15
00:02:16,440 --> 00:02:18,570
Since when did you become so generous?

16
00:02:20,120 --> 00:02:20,880
Ruirui.

17
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:23,240
You have privileges.

18
00:02:23,240 --> 00:02:25,240
I bought you two bottles of

19
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:26,810
soda in different flavors.

20
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:28,980
Here you go.

21
00:02:30,040 --> 00:02:31,440
Is there soda for me?

22
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:37,240
Qiao Yan, you're finally back.

23
00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:38,200
Did you miss me?

24
00:02:38,400 --> 00:02:39,840
Of course I did.

25
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:40,480
Without you,

26
00:02:40,480 --> 00:02:42,320
our group feels incomplete.

27
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,560
So the unpredictability of life

28
00:02:46,840 --> 00:02:48,600
is not just a phrase.

29
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:50,130
These past few days,

30
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:52,410
my mood has been like a roller coaster.

31
00:02:52,720 --> 00:02:55,320
Ups and downs.

32
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:57,570
I suddenly realized

33
00:02:57,800 --> 00:02:59,200
that the people around us

34
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,850
can really leave suddenly,

35
00:03:01,160 --> 00:03:02,620
and also return suddenly.

36
00:03:03,040 --> 00:03:06,440
We are completely helpless in the face of this impermanence.

37
00:03:06,640 --> 00:03:08,640
All we can do is cherish the present

38
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:11,080
and cherish everyone around us.

39
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:13,400
But what happened next

40
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:16,200
made me realize just how fragile life is.

41
00:03:16,480 --> 00:03:19,160
Sometimes people leave without even saying goodbye,

42
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,890
and they truly never come back.

43
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,530
The subscriber you dialed is out of the service area.

44
00:03:29,120 --> 00:03:29,920
How is it?

45
00:03:30,120 --> 00:03:31,520
Did Xiaoyu answer the phone?

46
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:34,380
They were sent to the disaster area for relief work.

47
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:36,560
Is it dangerous?

48
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:38,040
I trust him.

49
00:03:38,720 --> 00:03:40,980
I believe he can take good care of himself

50
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:42,840
and the victims as well.

51
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:46,720
Let's just stay at home and wait for news.

52
00:03:51,400 --> 00:03:54,440
So many people died in this earthquake.

53
00:03:54,880 --> 00:03:55,960
It's so tragic.

54
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:59,160
Look at these young children.

55
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,240
What are they going to do?

56
00:04:02,160 --> 00:04:04,280
I want to go to Wenchuan and join the rescue team.

57
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,640
This is nonsense.

58
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:09,320
Why would a student like you join a rescue team?

59
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,560
The government will send people.

60
00:04:10,560 --> 00:04:12,920
Just focus on your studies and stop overthinking.

61
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:15,650
On the way back, I thought about it the whole time.

62
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:18,579
The country educates us and sends us to college.

63
00:04:18,880 --> 00:04:20,209
Isn't it so that one day,

64
00:04:20,360 --> 00:04:21,240
we can contribute to our country

65
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,000
and society,

66
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:23,840
doing our part?

67
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,340
They need people there right now.

68
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,600
I think I should go.

69
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,560
What can you do if you go?

70
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:31,760
Can you do rescue work,

71
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:33,290
or help people move things?

72
00:04:33,320 --> 00:04:34,720
Aren't you just messing around?

73
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,080
I can be a volunteer.

74
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,320
I can help distribute supplies.

75
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,840
I can also help take care of the wounded.

76
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:40,840
I can move bricks.

77
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:41,840
I can do anything.

78
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:43,560
What is wrong with you?

79
00:04:43,760 --> 00:04:45,440
When did you suddenly become so stubborn?

80
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:46,760
Ever since he went to Zhicheng,

81
00:04:46,760 --> 00:04:48,000
he's become like this.

82
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:49,920
Look how he's mingled with those kids.

83
00:04:49,920 --> 00:04:51,640
Please don't be prejudiced against them.

84
00:04:51,640 --> 00:04:52,570
What prejudice?

85
00:04:53,640 --> 00:04:56,300
Look at the grades of the students in your class.

86
00:04:56,960 --> 00:04:59,080
Alright, then tell me,

87
00:04:59,240 --> 00:05:01,720
what exactly is so good about these kids?

88
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:06,800
Some of them, to inherit their father's legacy,

89
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:10,400
choose to join the army and defend the country.

90
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:12,040
Is that not good?

91
00:05:12,520 --> 00:05:13,400
Some of them,

92
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,860
to save a classmate with depression,

93
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,600
didn't hesitate to fall off a cliff together,

94
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,000
saving a life and a family.

95
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,960
Is that not good?

96
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,760
They helped two lonely elderly people

97
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:25,290
regain their passion and confidence in life.

98
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,880
Are they really

99
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:28,560
not good?

100
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:33,280
You used to say that having money and power is good,

101
00:05:33,280 --> 00:05:34,640
and being first is good.

102
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:37,080
But ever since I went to Zhicheng

103
00:05:37,240 --> 00:05:38,800
and met them, I realized

104
00:05:39,520 --> 00:05:41,850
there are many kinds of good in this world.

105
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,240
Some kinds of good

106
00:05:45,120 --> 00:05:45,960
are greater

107
00:05:46,880 --> 00:05:48,080
and more meaningful.

108
00:05:49,560 --> 00:05:50,360
And what I need

109
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:53,400
is exactly that kind of good.

110
00:05:54,800 --> 00:05:55,860
Do you understand?

111
00:06:16,280 --> 00:06:18,400
Stop hiding it. I saw everything.

112
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:22,520
You little brat. You've grown up.

113
00:06:30,320 --> 00:06:32,040
As for going to Wenchuan,

114
00:06:32,440 --> 00:06:33,880
don't even think about it.

115
00:06:33,880 --> 00:06:35,840
The situation there is very dangerous right now.

116
00:06:35,840 --> 00:06:36,880
Your mother and I

117
00:06:37,000 --> 00:06:38,560
only have one precious son.

118
00:06:38,960 --> 00:06:41,020
We will never let you take such a risk.

119
00:06:41,520 --> 00:06:42,120
All right.

120
00:06:54,120 --> 00:06:54,880
Your school

121
00:06:54,920 --> 00:06:57,040
will definitely organize a donation tomorrow.

122
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,280
Take this money

123
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:01,000
and donate it along with your pocket money.

124
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,520
Consider it a contribution to the country

125
00:07:02,520 --> 00:07:04,080
and the people of Wenchuan.

126
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,960
Brat, stop overthinking.

127
00:07:09,680 --> 00:07:11,480
Study hard and rest early.

128
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:15,610
Remember to give the check to your teacher tomorrow.

129
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:17,600
I know.

130
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,000
Thank you.

131
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:40,720
On May 12th, the eighth day of the fourth lunar month,

132
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,460
a massive 7.8 magnitude earthquake struck the Wenchuan area.

133
00:07:45,080 --> 00:07:46,360
In the face of this great disaster,

134
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:49,420
when one place is in trouble, help comes from all sides.

135
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:51,520
We gather here today

136
00:07:52,480 --> 00:07:54,680
not only to mourn our lost compatriots,

137
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:57,400
but also to pray for the living.

138
00:07:58,120 --> 00:08:00,400
May there be no more pain for those in heaven.

139
00:08:00,400 --> 00:08:02,600
May the living pull themselves together

140
00:08:02,600 --> 00:08:04,460
and embrace a brand new tomorrow.

141
00:08:05,600 --> 00:08:07,880
Please light the candles in your hands

142
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:12,880
and let us observe a three-minute silence for the deceased.

143
00:08:24,760 --> 00:08:26,040
This disaster

144
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,760
has taken away too many precious lives.

145
00:08:29,640 --> 00:08:31,880
Although I haven't seen it with my own eyes,

146
00:08:31,880 --> 00:08:33,480
I can feel the pain.

147
00:08:34,480 --> 00:08:35,720
It is said that only after experiencing sorrow

148
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:37,200
do we know how to cherish.

149
00:08:38,360 --> 00:08:39,320
Yes.

150
00:08:40,320 --> 00:08:41,760
At this moment,

151
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:44,960
they can still stand properly by my side.

152
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:50,000
We all still have healthy and safe families.

153
00:08:51,080 --> 00:08:53,400
What a lucky thing it is.

154
00:08:57,640 --> 00:08:58,640
Before,

155
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:01,600
I thought 'compatriot' was just a word.

156
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:03,600
At this moment,

157
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:07,720
this word seems to have seeped into our souls,

158
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:09,480
taken on flesh and blood,

159
00:09:10,040 --> 00:09:12,160
and become vivid lives

160
00:09:12,960 --> 00:09:14,640
that tug at our heartstrings.

161
00:09:49,880 --> 00:09:53,280
2008 was truly an extraordinary year,

162
00:09:54,080 --> 00:09:56,140
filled with reluctance and emotion.

163
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:57,600
Mutou and I

164
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,920
seem to have grown up a lot in an instant.

165
00:10:00,360 --> 00:10:02,360
But more surprises and wonders

166
00:10:02,600 --> 00:10:05,400
have actually just begun.

167
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:22,000
This... this is too unreal.

168
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,620
This is Mr. Zhen Shuai.

169
00:10:27,920 --> 00:10:29,050
Yuanbao, say hello.

170
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,400
Hello.

171
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,520
Hello, Mr. Zhen.

172
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,560
Hello.

173
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,600
Summer vacation is coming soon.

174
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,760
From now on, every weekend, Mr. Zhen

175
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:43,240
will come to tutor you two in physics and math.

176
00:10:43,240 --> 00:10:44,440
Three hours a day.

177
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:46,000
You two need to work hard.

178
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,280
Got it, Auntie.

179
00:10:49,680 --> 00:10:52,800
Mr. Zhen is a student at Qingbei University.

180
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:55,240
He got excellent grades back then

181
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:57,160
and got admitted to a university in Beijing.

182
00:10:57,160 --> 00:11:00,400
He is very experienced with the 12th grade and the college entrance exam.

183
00:11:00,400 --> 00:11:01,330
And he is about to

184
00:11:01,400 --> 00:11:03,360
prepare for the graduate school entrance exam.

185
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:05,640
He is just using his spare time

186
00:11:05,840 --> 00:11:07,080
to work part-time.

187
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,360
Right?

188
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,570
Yes, Auntie.

189
00:11:09,840 --> 00:11:11,960
I work part-time every winter and summer vacation

190
00:11:11,960 --> 00:11:13,120
to give high school students

191
00:11:13,120 --> 00:11:14,380
one-on-one tutoring.

192
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:16,480
Sharing some of my study methods

193
00:11:16,520 --> 00:11:18,450
and exam experience with everyone

194
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:19,960
is very meaningful to me.

195
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,360
Oh my god.

196
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:23,570
Zhen Shuai is really handsome.

197
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:26,040
Will Yuanbao be smitten?

198
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:26,960
Um,

199
00:11:27,160 --> 00:11:29,160
Mr. Zhen, let's go to that room for class.

200
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:29,800
Okay, Auntie.

201
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,240
You two get ready quickly. Class is starting.

202
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,360
This way, this way.

203
00:11:35,680 --> 00:11:37,080
Study hard with me.

204
00:11:37,160 --> 00:11:38,320
Don't be boy-crazy.

205
00:11:39,080 --> 00:11:40,210
I'll test you later.

206
00:11:40,520 --> 00:11:42,000
Got it. You're so nagging.

207
00:11:42,080 --> 00:11:43,120
Hurry up, you two.

208
00:11:43,120 --> 00:11:44,400
Okay, coming.

209
00:11:46,080 --> 00:11:47,200
Actually, let's look

210
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:49,520
at the trend charts for Person A and Person B.

211
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,160
Using the method we showed,

212
00:11:51,240 --> 00:11:53,480
A and B are both ruled out, right?

213
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,960
Then let's look at C.

214
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,280
Then option C.

215
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:01,320
Bro, you know what?

216
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:03,240
There was a top student in our school.

217
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:04,520
He came back to do a part-time job

218
00:12:04,520 --> 00:12:06,680
during the holiday to tutor the seniors.

219
00:12:06,680 --> 00:12:08,920
My cousin happened to be his student.

220
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:11,560
Not only did he help my cousin get into his school,

221
00:12:11,560 --> 00:12:13,360
but they also ended up together.

222
00:12:14,200 --> 00:12:18,160
That's what you call a double harvest in love and studies.

223
00:12:18,920 --> 00:12:19,920
How interesting.

224
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,440
What's wrong?

225
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:28,880
I need to use the restroom.

226
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:34,730
Let's continue.

227
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,160
For this one,

228
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:38,920
Option B, none are equal.

229
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,160
We can rule this one out too.

230
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:42,560
Why are you back already?

231
00:12:43,720 --> 00:12:44,580
I lost the urge.

232
00:12:47,080 --> 00:12:49,410
Do you find the questions a bit difficult?

233
00:12:50,160 --> 00:12:53,560
Actually, learning math consists of three main parts.

234
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,840
First is learning the concepts.

235
00:12:56,320 --> 00:12:57,240
We need to clearly understand

236
00:12:57,240 --> 00:12:59,100
all the concepts in the textbook,

237
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:01,280
and apply them flexibly.

238
00:13:01,880 --> 00:13:04,810
Then the second point is the sea of questions tactic.

239
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:08,080
If he tutors Ruirui,

240
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,760
she will definitely faint from happiness.

241
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,280
Mr. Zhen Shuai is so handsome.

242
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:34,530
What's wrong? Are you feeling unwell?

243
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:38,000
Not at all. I'm feeling great.

244
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,100
Fifty students in a class,

245
00:13:45,120 --> 00:13:47,320
in a 100-meter test,

246
00:13:47,600 --> 00:13:49,730
their results are shown in the figure.

247
00:13:49,760 --> 00:13:50,800
So let's see,

248
00:13:50,840 --> 00:13:53,300
the results of the first two students are...

249
00:13:58,600 --> 00:13:59,280
Sir.

250
00:14:00,560 --> 00:14:04,400
Um, you should head back

251
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,920
and get some rest.

252
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,040
It's fine.

253
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,280
Don't worry about the time.

254
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:11,340
I'm more than willing to help you out.

255
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,410
Sir, your words are so helpful.

256
00:14:16,520 --> 00:14:18,280
Can I ask you a few more questions?

257
00:14:18,280 --> 00:14:19,160
Sure, go ahead.

258
00:14:21,360 --> 00:14:22,080
Yuanbao.

259
00:14:23,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Don't you want to go to the restroom?

260
00:14:26,920 --> 00:14:28,040
I don't want to.

261
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:29,520
I haven't had much water.

262
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:37,010
Look at the question first.

263
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:49,650
Sir, I'm going to the restroom.

264
00:14:50,560 --> 00:14:51,960
Sir, could you give me

265
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:52,800
your chat ID

266
00:14:52,840 --> 00:14:54,080
or phone number?

267
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:55,160
In case I have any questions later.

268
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:56,120
Right.

269
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:57,680
You should leave a chat ID, sir.

270
00:14:57,680 --> 00:14:58,480
Just add mine.

271
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:00,800
We will both ask you if we don't understand something.

272
00:15:00,800 --> 00:15:01,400
Okay.

273
00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:06,160
Here.

274
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:07,080
Okay.

275
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:14,480
This question is the last one in the college entrance exam.

276
00:15:14,480 --> 00:15:17,740
So my predictions are actually quite accurate every year.

277
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:27,010
We use our rule of probability.

278
00:15:28,680 --> 00:15:29,280
Sir.

279
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:31,400
You've been talking for so long.

280
00:15:31,400 --> 00:15:33,000
Are you bursting to go?

281
00:15:33,200 --> 00:15:33,680
Do you not know

282
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:34,840
where our bathroom is?

283
00:15:34,840 --> 00:15:35,120
No.

284
